The Chamber of the Starmoon Casket: Built into the base of the eastern mesa wall is a small, low structure of pale, ancient stone — the Chamber of the Starmoon Casket. This is the sacred repository where the astrologers guard their most treasured relic. The chamber’s single, iron‑bound door is sealed with a great silver lock, and through a narrow, slit‑like window, the faint, cyan‑white glow of the Casket itself can be seen pulsing within.

The Ancient Love’s Memorial: At the valley’s western edge, a single, petrified olive tree stands beside a small, dry fountain. A worn, ancient stone bench sits beneath the tree. This is the Ancient Love’s Memorial, the place where, according to the memories Esmeralda received from the first astrologers, a great astrologer and the tyrant Khufra once sat together, before his fall into greed and darkness. A single, faint, ghostly vine of pale gold still clings to the stone.

Esmeralda — The Astrologer (Tiny, Radiant Silhouette): Standing at the edge of the Great Observatory’s platform, her form rendered with exquisite, miniature precision, is a single silhouette of Esmeralda herself. She is a young woman, her figure slender and graceful in a flowing, hooded robe of deep indigo and silver. Her hood is partially lowered, revealing long, dark hair that catches the starlight. In her hands, she holds a large, open astrologer’s tome, its pages glowing with the same faint, cyan‑white light as the Starmoon Casket. Beside her, floating in the air, is the opened Starmoon Casket itself — a small, ornate box of silver and gold, from which two distinct streams of power, Frostmoon (pale blue) and Stardust (glowing silver), flow outward and center around her. Her posture is one of quiet, focused study, her gaze fixed on the heavens. A tiny vermilion label floats beside the Observatory.

The Astrologer’s Path: A single, straight, silver‑stone road — the Astrologer’s Path — connects the Gate of the Star‑Readers to the Great Observatory, its surface inscribed with the names of every astrologer who has ever served.

The Distant Desert: Beyond the mesas, the vast, darkening desert stretches to the horizon, with the faint, distant glow of the Emerald Road to the north and the jagged, volcanic silhouette of Fire Throat far to the south‑west.

