The Tomb of Khufra (The Sarcophagus of the Tyrant): At the exact centre of the courtyard, rising from the black obsidian floor, is the Tomb of Khufra. It is not a grand pyramid, but a single, massive, upright sarcophagus carved from a block of pale, luminous amber‑gold stone, its surface polished to a mirror sheen. The sarcophagus is carved in the likeness of a noble, handsome young prince, but its surface is criss‑crossed by thick, heavy chains of tarnished silver, and wrapped in a living, writhing net of enchanted teal bandages, their golden glyphs pulsing with a slow, rhythmic heartbeat. From within the sealed stone, a faint, sickly amber light bleeds outward, the enduring life‑force of the tyrant.

